<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="7" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1872,2014]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,152,216]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="7" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicName box="[151,367,1872,1897]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Basiliolidae" genus="Basiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="beecheri">
<emphasis box="[151,367,1872,1897]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Basiliola beecheri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of five rhynchonellides in the investigated material. Species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1205,1392,1872,1898]" class="Rhynchonellata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="order">Rhynchonellida</taxonomicName>
are characterized by a very simple brachial skeleton in the form of two short processes or crura. The presence of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,285,1949,1974]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Basiliolidae" genus="Basiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="beecheri">
<emphasis box="[151,285,1949,1974]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">B. beecheri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the 
<collectingCountry box="[374,467,1949,1975]" name="Norfolk Island" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Norfolk</collectingCountry>
Ridge was already noted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Laurin" box="[810,974,1949,1975]" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" refString="Laurin, B. (1997) Brachiopodes recoltes dans les eaux de la Nouvelle Caledonie et des iles Loyaute, Matthew et Chesterfield. In: Crosnier, A. (ed.), Resultats des Campagnes MUSORSTOM. Volume 18. Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, 176, 411 - 471." type="journal article" year="1997">
Laurin (
<number box="[905,966,1949,1975]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1997.0">1997</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Zezina" box="[1033,1202,1949,1975]" pageId="5" pageNumber="33" refString="Zezina, O. N. (2005) On the systematic position of some Recent brachiopod species from the Norfolk Ridge (West Pacific). Invertebrate Zoology, 2, 29 - 33. [In Russian with English summary]." type="journal article" year="2005">
Zezina (
<number box="[1129,1193,1949,1975]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. It was found on 
<number box="[1407,1436,1949,1975]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="10.0">10</number>
seamounts (
<tableCitation box="[298,405,1988,2014]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,240,689,713]" captionText="TABLE 1. Comparative species diversity on the seamounts as sampled by different cruises (Norfolk 1 and Norfolk 2)" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Tables 
<number box="[389,405,1988,2014]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1.2">1</number>
</tableCitation>
, 2) with a depth range of 
<quantity box="[732,886,1988,2014]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.33" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="2.66" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="m" value="633.0" valueMax="1000.0" valueMin="266.0">266–1000 m</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[905,999,1988,2014]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="27.[151,255,1303,1327]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,194,1278]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,194,1279]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 14. Depth ranges of particular brachiopod species collected during the Norfolk 1 and Norfolk 2 cruises to the Norfolk Ridge, New Caledonia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190412/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Fig. 
<number box="[964,999,1988,2014]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[1022,1251,1988,2013]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Basiliolidae" genus="Basiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="beecheri">
<emphasis box="[1022,1251,1988,2013]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Basiliola beecheri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described from Hawaii (
<bibRefCitation author="Dall" box="[455,585,152,178]" pageId="6" pageNumber="31" refString="Dall, W. H. (1895) Report on the Mollusca and Brachiopoda dredged in deep water, chiefly near the Hawaiian Islands, with ilustrations of hitherto unfigured species from northwest America. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 17, 675 - 733." type="journal article" year="1895">
Dall 
<number box="[519,585,152,178]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1895.0">1895</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Cooper" box="[598,763,152,178]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="31" pageId="6" pageNumber="30" refString="Cooper, G. A. (1959) Genera of Tertiary and Recent rhynchonelloid brachiopods. Smithsonian Miscellaneous Collections, 139, 1 - 90." type="journal article" year="1959">
Cooper 
<number box="[698,763,152,178]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1959.0">1959</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Zezina" box="[778,949,152,178]" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" refString="Zezina, O. N. (1981 b) The composition and the ways of formation of the thalassobathyal brachiopod fauna. In: Zuznetsov, A. P. &amp; Mironov, N. A. (eds), Benhos of the submarine mountains Marcus-Necket and adjacent Pacific regions. Academy of Sciences of the USSR, P. P. Shirshov Institute of Oceanology, Moscow, pp. 141 - 149. [In Russian with English summary]" type="book chapter" year="1981" yearSuffix="b">
Zezina 
<number box="[871,933,152,178]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1981.0">1981</number>
b
</bibRefCitation>
) but has also been recorded from 
<collectingCountry name="New Caledonia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[326,367,190,216]" name="Fiji" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fiji</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Laurin" box="[382,532,190,216]" pageId="6" pageNumber="31" refString="Laurin, B. (1997) Brachiopodes recoltes dans les eaux de la Nouvelle Caledonie et des iles Loyaute, Matthew et Chesterfield. In: Crosnier, A. (ed.), Resultats des Campagnes MUSORSTOM. Volume 18. Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, 176, 411 - 471." type="journal article" year="1997">
Laurin 
<number box="[470,532,190,216]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1997.0">1997</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bitner" box="[544,701,190,216]" pageId="6" pageNumber="30" refString="Bitner, M. A. (2006 b) Recent Brachiopoda from the Fiji and Wallis and Futuna Islands, Southwest Pacific. In: Justine, J. L. &amp; Richer de Forges, B. (eds), Tropical Deep Sea Benthos. Volume 24. Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, 193, 15 - 32." type="journal article" year="2006" yearSuffix="b">
Bitner 
<number box="[624,686,190,216]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2006.0">2006</number>
b
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<number box="[712,776,190,216]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2008.0">2008</number>
).
</paragraph>
